This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as speech recognition and machine translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for enforcing modularity in seq2seq models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of AI models. It could also be categorized under cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it is inspired by modular software design principles. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a method for improving the performance of neural network models.
